{"lemma":"طِوالُ","slug":"طِوالُ","root":"ط.#.ل","root_slug":"ط-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ل","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طَوِيل","root":"طول","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27357","n27358","n27364"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%90%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"long, tall"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Late CaCīC-type adjective from the root ط و ل (ṭ w l). Were this an ancient word, it would instead be expected to have the form *طَيِّل (*ṭayyil) per the sound shifts described at جَيِّد (jayyid, “good”), so the form طَوِيل (ṭawīl) indicates a later formation from after said sound shifts had ceased to operate.\nUltimately from Proto-Afroasiatic *ṭVwl- (“long, far”). Cognate with Egyptian dwn (“to stretch out, to be stretched out”)."},"ipa":["/tˤa.wiːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27357","headword_ar":"طَوَالٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwlN","text_ar":"طُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwalN","text_ar":"طِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27358","headword_ar":"طُوَالٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawiylN","text_ar":"طَوِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuw~aAlN","text_ar":"طُوَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27364","headword_ar":"طُوَّالٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Very,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceedingly, tall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;) applied to a man; as also, in the same sense, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwaAlN","text_ar":"طُوَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) the latter having a stronger signification than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawiylN","text_ar":"طَوِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [with which it is mentioned above as syn.,] (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiykN","text_ar":"رَكِيكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or it denotes less than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuw~aAlN","text_ar":"طُوَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zrf","text_ar":"ظرف"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwlaAniY~N","text_ar":"طُولَانِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTaAwilN","text_ar":"مُطَاوِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the dial. of the vulgar:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuw~aAlN","text_ar":"طُوَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has no broken pl., its pl. being only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuw~aAluwna","text_ar":"طُوَّالُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": its fem. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so is that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwaAlN","text_ar":"طُوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; each applied to a woman. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]}}